00:08:34.760 --> 00:08:38.215
Let's talk about VPATs and ACRs.

00:08:38.360 --> 00:08:41.519
What is the difference
between a VPAT and ACR?

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:43.759
Really, it's very, very easy.

00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:47.679
The VPAT is what you download
from the internet,

00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:52.199
and the ACR is what you send
to people or what a vendor sends to you.

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:54.599
The VPAT is basically the full template.

00:08:54.600 --> 00:09:01.040
The ACR is the filled-out template,
is the short version of that.

00:09:02.280 --> 00:09:05.399
I'm going to use
the term ACR instead of VPAT,

00:09:05.400 --> 00:09:11.880
even though the term VPAT
is more commonly used.

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:16.679
When I'm talking about an ACR,
it's the filled-out version,

00:09:16.680 --> 00:09:19.490
but they are used interchangeably.

00:09:20.080 --> 00:09:22.719
Basically, what is an ACR?

00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:26.639
It's an explanation of the accessibility
compliance of a product.

00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:31.559
It's not a sales document,
even though it often gets used as one.

00:09:31.560 --> 00:09:36.239
It's basically a point in time
where it says this is,

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:37.399
at this point in time,

00:09:37.400 --> 00:09:41.605
where the accessibility compliance
of this product is.

00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:42.839
We've got these issues,

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:46.879
we don't have those issues,
we fix these things.

00:09:46.880 --> 00:09:51.800
It's owned and often assessed
or created by the product vendor,

00:09:51.880 --> 00:09:56.399
but it's always more, I believe,

00:09:56.400 --> 00:10:00.359
if there's a third-party that does
the assessment.

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:04.119
In order to fill out the ACR properly,
you really need to conduct

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:06.919
a complete accessibility
audit on a product.

00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:08.999
It's not just a case of filling
out a document.

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:12.519
You have to do quite extensive
testing to determine

00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:14.279
where the accessibility compliance

00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:18.539
of the document is to then fill
out the ACR.

00:10:19.320 --> 00:10:21.979
It's required by Section 508 in the US

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:24.439
and almost all federal solicitations.

00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:28.010
It's very common
in universities and colleges.

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:32.319
Even in Australia, it's something
that we sometimes can request

00:10:32.320 --> 00:10:36.279
or my clients request because it gives

00:10:36.280 --> 00:10:40.339
an idea of where
the accessibility compliance is

00:10:40.340 --> 00:10:45.576
and what people have done to meet
those accessibility requirements.

00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:48.359
It's not actually, though,

00:10:48.360 --> 00:10:51.359
an accessibility audit
report of a product.

00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:53.639
It tells you what
the accessibility compliance is,

00:10:53.640 --> 00:10:56.799
but it's not actually an audit report.

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:58.839
It's not only for government.

00:10:58.840 --> 00:11:01.639
It's something
that can be used by everyone.

00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:03.119
It's not only for web products.

00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:06.960
You can actually get
an ACR for your photocopier

00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:11.039
or your smart TV or something like that.

00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:14.159
It's, unfortunately, not always accurate.

00:11:14.160 --> 00:11:16.479
I'll talk about that in a moment.

00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:19.971
It's not a good indicator
of ATAG compliance.

00:11:20.360 --> 00:11:23.519
Now, ATAG is the Authoring
Tool Accessibility Guidelines,

00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:27.119
very different to the Web
Content Accessibility Guidelines.

00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:29.639
The Authoring
Tool Accessibility Guidelines,

00:11:29.640 --> 00:11:33.759
you'd want to apply them
or test them when you're dealing

00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:38.079
with anything that's author's content,
so WordPress, for example.

00:11:38.080 --> 00:11:42.999
An ACR of WordPress
is not necessarily a good indicator

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:47.120
of ATAG compliance
for that particular product.

00:11:48.520 --> 00:11:52.719
There are different categories,
web products, operating systems,

00:11:52.720 --> 00:11:55.039
desktop software, photocopiers,

00:11:55.040 --> 00:11:58.902
telephones, tablets,
smartphones, et cetera.

00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:02.039
Then when it comes
to the sections of an ACR,

00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:04.850
they're always the same, no matter

00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:11.039
what you're testing until you get further
on into the WCAG section.

00:12:11.040 --> 00:12:15.079
The first section is title,
which should be the company name,

00:12:15.080 --> 00:12:18.079
and then accessibility conformance report,

00:12:18.080 --> 00:12:20.519
name of the product, and the version.

00:12:20.520 --> 00:12:22.579
Now, the version,
it's really important to have

00:12:22.580 --> 00:12:27.463
that information
because if you have an ACR on Version 2.4,

00:12:27.840 --> 00:12:30.599
but you're actually implementing
Version 3.5,

00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:34.039
then that ACR
is not going to be very accurate.

00:12:34.040 --> 00:12:36.639
It's also important that
there's a product description,

00:12:36.640 --> 00:12:40.519
and it's important that this is
a good product description.

00:12:40.520 --> 00:12:44.119
I've looked at hundreds,
maybe thousands of ACRs,

00:12:44.120 --> 00:12:46.930
and a lot of them are very salesy.

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:51.359
It's really important that, as I said,
it's not a sales document,

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:52.919
it's actual description

00:12:52.920 --> 00:12:57.440
of what it is that the ACR
or what the product does.

00:12:57.640 --> 00:12:59.376
Then the report date.

00:13:00.640 --> 00:13:03.359
It's important to look
at that as well and determine

00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:07.881
whether you're happy
with how old the ACR is.

00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:10.799
Then there's also contact information.

00:13:10.800 --> 00:13:13.679
It's always important, I think,

00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:17.479
to have a phone number
as well as an email address

00:13:17.480 --> 00:13:20.999
for an actual human
and a human person's name,

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:25.119
as opposed to accessibility
at wordpress.org or something

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:28.279
like that so that there
is actually one person

00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:32.720
who is responsible
for this and that can be contacted.

00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:35.159
It's also important that that person

00:13:35.160 --> 00:13:41.040
has the ability and the time to actually
respond to any questions

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:44.988
about the ACR.

00:13:45.360 --> 00:13:46.639
Then there's notes.

00:13:46.640 --> 00:13:50.519
Notes often will mention
things that might be excluded

00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:55.280
or maybe some information
about when fixes will be completed,

00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:58.199
and then the evaluation methods used.

00:13:58.200 --> 00:14:00.719
This is really, really important.

00:14:00.720 --> 00:14:05.679
Evaluation methods used should talk
about automated testing tools,

00:14:05.680 --> 00:14:08.279
automated accessibility testing tools,

00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:11.599
as well as manual accessibility testing,

00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:15.839
as well as some assistive
technology testing,

00:14:15.840 --> 00:14:20.839
including mobile and including
mobile assistive technology testing.

00:14:20.840 --> 00:14:25.119
Often, we use these automated
accessibility testing tools.

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:28.294
We did this manual testing and we tested

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:33.120
with JAWS on Windows and NVDA on Windows.

00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:36.599
Then the question is,
well, what about Mac users?

00:14:36.600 --> 00:14:40.639
Then the question is,
how does this work on a mobile phone?

00:14:40.640 --> 00:14:44.607
Then you have the report information
and the terms.

00:14:44.880 --> 00:14:49.239
The accessibility section
of the ACR is really--

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:53.207
there's tables for each WCAG
standard or guideline.

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:58.539
There's a table for WCAG 2, 2.1, or 2.2,

00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:00.884
depending on how old the ACR is.

00:15:00.885 --> 00:15:04.679
There's a table for Level A,
table for Level AA.

00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:07.439
I haven't yet seen an ACR
that has a table for AAA,

00:15:07.440 --> 00:15:09.479
but you can have it there if you want.

00:15:09.480 --> 00:15:13.779
Then there's additional sections
for Section 508 requirements,

00:15:13.780 --> 00:15:16.057
if the person uses it.

